":["English:  see  Skidmore  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Skidmore","meanings":["English (Staffordshire): of Norman origin, a variant of <b>Scudamore</b>, which most probably arises from a Norman French nickname for a knight who used a particular type of leather shield, from the unrecorded Norman French phrase, <i>escu de more</i> ‘Moor's shield’, a reference to a type of Moorish leather shield called an <i>adarga</i>, which was in widespread use not only in medieval Iberia and north Africa but also in Brittany.","History: The manor of Upton Scudamore in Wiltshire was held by Peter de Skydemore in 1216. The same manor was held by Godfrey Escudamore shortly after 1150. The Scudamore family claim descent from Ralph, recorded in Domesday Book (1086) as holder of <i>Opeton</i> (Upton), whose son was known as Reginald <i>Escudemor</i>."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":41,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":50,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":85,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":116,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter Scudamore was born about 1174, in Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, his father, Elias de Scudamore, was 28 and his mother, Lady Elias Scudamore, was 27. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Sybil."},"et":{"about 1174–":"umbes 1174–Surnud","1174–Male":"1174–Surnud","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","1197–1266":"1197–1266","1227–Female":"1227–Surnud","1148–1191":"1148–1191","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1264":"1264","1197":"1197","1174":"1174","1290":"1290","1191":"1191","1227":"1227","1205":"1205","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1148":"1148","1224":"1224","1266":"1266","1200":"1200","about 1227":"umbes 1227","about 1174":"umbes 1174","Abbey Dore, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Abbey Dore, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England":"Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1174–":"noin 1174–Kuollut","1174–Male":"1174–Kuollut","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","1197–1266":"1197